Where in North Dakota Is Carmen Sandiego?

[edit]

Very interesting discovery for me, as a lover of the Carmen Sandiego franchise. This state-specific game has scant sources on the internet, yet is a very fascinating piece of gaming history.--Coin945 (talk)

Oppose due to low page view stats and Low importance in WikiProject Video games. --Rubbish computer (HALP!: I dropped the bass?)

FWIW, I wouldn't base any decisions on the "importance" scale. Firstly, I find this scale very dubious personally and having little actual value due to the subjectivity of it all and lack of regulation. Secondly, most of the articles I nominated are very new, and the talk page templates were added swiftly after creation; the "Low" importance is the default choice despite it actually being true or not.--Coin945 (talk)

Support - per nomination.--BabbaQ (talk)

Oppose – Per the article, it's the "arguably the least-known title in the franchise". As such, it is unpopular, and the article receives low page views: 191 views in the last 30 days. Unlikely to attract much interest. North America1000

Oppose – As User:Northamerica1000 said, it's probably too obscure to secure enough interest. Graham (talk)

{{Unapproved}}. No further input after 21 days. North America1000
